div.p:
In addition to these differences, there are major intelligence community
                        disagreements concerning: 

—the enemy order of battle;

—the importance of Cambodia (in particular Sihanoukville) as a
                                supply channel for the enemy;

—the impact of possible Vietnam outcomes on Southeast Asia.

The major points of agreement within the U.S. Government on these subjects are:
—the description of recent U.S. deployments and tactics;
—the difficulties of assessing the results of B–52 strikes, but their effectiveness against known troop concentrations and in close support operations;
—the fact that the Soviets and Chinese supply almost all war material to Hanoi and have enabled the North Vietnamese to carry on despite all our operations.
